# Railway Platform v1.0 — preserve byte-exact content for the SHA-256-pinned
# regression baseline. Disabling EOL normalization guarantees a fresh clone
# reproduces the golden hashes (railway/tests/regression/golden_output_manifest.csv).
* -text
*.pbix binary
*.xlsx binary
*.ipynb -text

# STEP36: output CSVs + golden manifest are normalized to LF so the SHA-256 manifest
# is reproducible across OS (CI is Linux/LF; pandas writes CRLF on Windows). git
# normalizes these on add/checkout regardless of how they were written.
railway/outputs/**/*.csv text eol=lf
railway/tests/regression/golden_output_manifest.csv text eol=lf
